From 301cc10ccff319619233c42e7a12e8ab1a4f9cb7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aloka Dixit <aloka.dixit@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jan 2024 14:54:49 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/8] QSDK:CP:wifi:ath12k: support for PCIe link removal for ErP

Remove PCIE slots when QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_RM_GENERIC is
received with QCA_WLAN_VENDOR_ATTR_ERP_CONFIG_PCIE_REMOVE flag
and rescan removed PCIes during exit.

Process PCIe removal and rescan in a single threaded workqueue
using global work structure instance erp_pcie_config.
This synchronizes entry and exit operations. Keep critical
section at minimum in workqueue handler function by acquiring
erp_sm.lock only to retrieve and update enter_cnt and exit_cnt.
These counts are used by next vendor command from userspace to
decide if previous entry/exit are in progress.

Patch-dependency: 0425-01-QSDK-CP-wifi-ath12k-add-wake-up-trigger-for-ErP.patch

Signed-off-by: Aloka Dixit <aloka.dixit@oss.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Sidhanta Sahu <quic_sidhanta@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <aaradhana.sahu@oss.qualcomm.com>
